verbs.description: whoo (third-person singular simple present whoos, present participle whooing, simple past and past participle whooed)

entries.meaning: To make a whoo sound, of delight, whistling, or of an owl etc.
examples: "Upon my honour!" cried he, "there was never before such a beautiful thing in Nature or Art as you look, 'Cousin' Tess ('Cousin' had a faint ring of mockery). I have been watching you from over the wallâ€”sitting like Im-patience on a monument, and pouting up that pretty red mouth to whistling shape, and whooing and whooing, and privately swearing, and never being able to produce a note. Why, you are quite cross because you can't do it."
